{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XTdWE7bWQ3jjpKqWrUDkxm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The case resource files show that:\n1. There should be two ingress classes: `ingress-1` and `ingress-2`\n2. There should be a second ingress controller in `ingress-nginx-2` namespace using `ingress-2` class\n3. There should be a `demo-app` ingress in the `demo` namespace for `class.example.com` using `ingressClassName: ingress-2`\n\nBut looking at the current state:\n- The `demo-app` ingress exists but uses `ingressClassName: nginx` and serves `demo.example.com`\n- The `ingress-2` class doesn't exist yet\n- The second ingress controller in `ingress-nginx-2` namespace is missing\n\nSo the precondition setup hasn't been completed—I need to create both the second controller and its corresponding ingress class, then update the demo ingress to use the correct class and hostname.\n\nLet me look at the test.yaml to see what the precondition actually sets up versus what needs to be created.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2133,"cache_read_input_tokens":37826,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2133},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4b726287-89f1-42dc-85d0-35e674d51669","uuid":"9a2e075f-1f37-4694-a61d-9e3c3ac90330","request_id":"req_011CcN6GrSdAZgHtwyamxCmh"}
