Ingress working properly.\n\nFor the test to pass, I need three things: the `ingress-gateway` service in the `demo` namespace pointing to the `ingress-nginx-2` controller, the `ingress-nginx-2` controller running with the `ingress-2` class, and an ingress configured for `class.example.com`.\n\nLooking at what's missing, I need to create both IngressClasses, deploy the second nginx controller in its own namespace, set up the `ingress-gateway` ExternalName service, and create the ingress resource with the proper routing. Let me start by getting the controller image and working through these steps.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":423,"cache_read_input_tokens":51597,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":423},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4b726287-89f1-42dc-85d0-35e674d51669","uuid":"e4ed0dd6-8953-4f78-aa18-e45e1a9161e0","request_id":"req_011CcN6S1Tr8dMuyBYAhP1NG"}
